nodes.text: A Clone tank gunner served under Clone trooper commander CC-3636.

He served in the Second Battle of Felucia and manned an All Terrain Tactical Enforcer. He fired on the Confederacy of Independent Systems outpost on the planet with the Mass-driver cannon located on the top of the AT-TE on the order of Jedi General Plo Koon.

He was voiced, like all clone troopers, by Dee Bradley Baker. He only appeared in one episode of Star Wars: The Clone Wars. The helmet's markings was designed by David Filoni for a production asset called "Clone Pilot 104th", a Clone Pilot of the 104th Legion. This asset was never used and the helmet design ended up on this unidentified Clone Tank Gunner.
